warrantable.d:
a. Authorized by commission, precept, or right;
   justifiable; defensible; as, the seizure of a thief is always
   warrantable by law and justice; falsehood is never warrantable.

wattling.d:
p. pr. & vb. n. of Wattle
n. The act or process of binding or platting with twigs;
   also, the network so formed.
